  "texts": [
    "This study uses gpt -3.5-turbo to develop two few-shot learning models with subtle distinctions in training data selection.• LLM Random Within each prompt, n randomly selected samples were presented to this model, with n ranging from 0 to 70, and requested it to classify an unseen instance as either \"Benign\" or \"DDOS\".",
    "• LLM Top K Given an unlabelled data, we ranked training samples based on the Pinecone index and retrieved the top k on the list as few-shot examples for this model.",
    "Fine-tuned LLM:The base model for fine-tuning is the ada model.",
    "We formed each training data as a pair of prompt and response.",
    "The prompt contained the 4 features of one data point, and the corresponding label was isolated as the expected response."
  ],
